# Monkeyland Architecture

## WM Brain ‚Äî Event-Driven State Machine (Rust)

All WM decision logic lives in `src-tauri/src/wm_brain.rs`:

- `inspect_and_decide(env, project_path, active_agent_task_ids)` ‚Äî the core brain function
  - Lists tasks via `env.run_bd(path, &["list", "--json", "--all"])`
  - Detects and closes zombie/duplicate epics and tasks
  - Classifies state: `ProjectState::New`, `InProgress`, `Completed`, `Error`
  - Builds `state_context` (system prompt appendix) and `completion_summary`
  - Returns `InspectionResult` with full `Diagnostics`

- `decide_events(result)` ‚Äî converts InspectionResult to WmEvents
  - `Completed` ‚Üí `ShortCircuit` (no LLM)
  - `New` / `InProgress` ‚Üí `RunLlm` (with tools to remove)
  - `Error` ‚Üí `ShowError`

### State machine phases

`WmPhase`: Idle ‚Üí Inspecting ‚Üí Completed | SettingUp | Error
SettingUp ‚Üí Monitoring (via wm_llm_done)
Completed/Error/Monitoring ‚Üí Inspecting (via wm_handle_message)

### Tauri commands

- `wm_launch(prompt_text)` ‚Äî pauses orch, inspects, emits events
- `wm_handle_message(text)` ‚Äî same flow for follow-up messages
- `wm_llm_done(response_text)` ‚Äî transitions to Monitoring, starts orch
- `wm_llm_error(error)` ‚Äî transitions to Error
- `wm_get_state()` ‚Äî returns persisted WmState for frontend hydration

### Orchestration lifecycle (backend-owned)

- `wm_launch` ‚Üí `orch_pause()` before inspection
- `ShortCircuit` ‚Üí orch stays paused
- `RunLlm` ‚Üí orch stays paused while LLM runs
- `wm_llm_done` ‚Üí `orch_start()`
- App reload ‚Üí orch starts paused, user must interact to start

## Frontend ‚Äî Dumb Reducer

`src/wmReducer.ts` applies `WmEvent`s from the backend to produce `WmUiState`:

- Zero business logic ‚Äî just state transitions
- Event listener on `"wm_event"` feeds the reducer
- `RunLlm` event triggers LLM streaming (the one thing in TypeScript)
- On stream completion ‚Üí `invoke("wm_llm_done")`, on error ‚Üí `invoke("wm_llm_error")`

## Plugin system

Plugins extend LLM agent capabilities. Each plugin implements `Plugin` (src/plugins/Plugin.ts):
- `execute()` returns `{ result: string }` ‚Äî can also include `stopAgent: true` to abort the agent
- `PluginExecutionContext` provides `layouts` (canvas cards), `abortController` (to stop the agent)
- `toAiTool()` wraps execute for the Vercel AI SDK; auto-aborts controller if `stopAgent: true`

### Key principle: never trust the LLM for state management

- `[TERMINAL]` markers in tool results are hints, not guarantees ‚Äî LLMs ignore them
- Use `stopAgent: true` in plugin results to force-abort via the abortController
- Physical tool constraints (removing tools from plugin set) beat prompt instructions
- Pre-LLM deterministic checks (in Rust) beat in-LLM tool calls

## State detection

1. MetaDb stored path (`get_beads_project_path` ‚Äî persists across restarts)
2. Backend reads directly ‚Äî no IPC gap between logic and data
3. BeadsToolPlugin safety net (quick `bd list` check when `beads_init` returns "already initialized")

## Testing strategy

- Backend: `cargo test --lib wm_brain` ‚Äî full inspection chain with `TestWmEnv`
- Frontend: `npx vitest run wmReducer.test.ts` ‚Äî reducer with canned event sequences
- No frontend‚Üíbackend mocking needed ‚Äî the two sides test independently
